[h1]Q / A[/h1]
[b]Q[/b]: Is it VAC safe?
[b]A[/b]: Yes! Binary modules are NOT loaded to inside GMod. We only use interfaces that Valve has exposed and use GMod's own functions to communicate with talon voice.
Linux users will likely need injection, which is not fully VAC safe but should be okay.

[b]Q[/b]: Does it work with addon <x>?
[b]A[/b]: Make a pull request with commands! Talon commands are "easy" to create: https://github.com/Metastruct/talon_gmod/blob/dev/talon_user_additions/gmod_ulx.talon Also see [url=https://talon.wiki/]talon wiki[/url] for writing commands.


[b]Q[/b]: I have tried everything, but it does not work
[b]A[/b]: Check [url=https://github.com/Metastruct/talon_gmod#troubleshooting]troubleshooting[/url] and  [url=https://github.com/Metastruct/talon_gmod/issues]issues[/url].

[b]Q[/b]: Does server need to install anything?
[b]A[/b]: Unfortunately, yes, ask them to subscribe to this workshop addon or send this link: https://github.com/Metastruct/talon_gmod#for-servers--singleplayer--listen-server-users

